 British defence minister Gavin Williamson with Estonian defence minister Juri Luik in a joint news conference, Williamson saying Russian president Vladimir Putin is trying to drive the wedge between allies, Williamson saying British government is exploring options in response to alleged Russian poisoning of former double agent. Williamson said he is surprised by reports of European Commission planning to freeze Britain out of satellite navigation project due to BREXIT and that he hopes Commission ‘will not play politics’ on European defence and security. 